HEADWORD: Abactor
<hw>Ab*ac"tor</hw> <pr>(-t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>abigere</ets> to drive away; <ets>ab</ets> + <ets>agere</ets> to
drive.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One who steals and drives away
cattle or beasts by herds or droves.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Abaculus</ent>⟦br⟧
